title: afterword
body:
Also known as あとがき (atogaki) in Japanese. A literary device typically found at the end of a work.

The contents of the afterword tend to be from the author's perspective, giving insights on how the ideas for a work were formed, or how the work itself was created. Sometimes, someone other than the author may use the afterword to give commentary on the work's context (e.g. history or culture surrounding the setting).

title: little_sister_(elona)
body:
A quest character from [[Elona]].  In an "homage" to [[bioshock (series)|BioShock]], Little Sisters are capturable characters found by killing rarely spawning Big Daddy monsters, and can be returned to the Strange Scientist for rare items.  (Specifically, they are captured with "Little Balls", which are special Little Sister-only [[poke_ball|pokeballs]] in an homage to [[Pokemon]].) Because the items you get for the quest include duplicates of otherwise unique objects gained from other quests, they are extremely valuable.  Also in homage to the game, killing and eating a Little Sister grants the player extra Life, Mana, and skill potential, but counts as a "debt" of sisters you need to rescue to gain the rare items.  (This also counts if the little sister dies when you didn't kill her, yourself.)

They have [[black hair]] in a [[bob cut]] or [[hime cut]], depending on the artist, and wear a red [[dress]].

Not to be confused with the similarly-named [[younger_sister_(elona)|Younger Sister]].

title: marauder_(doom_eternal)
body: In [[Doom Eternal]], the Marauder is a former member of the Night Sentinels of Argenta, and part of the faction of Argenta that continues to serve the Khan Maykr despite the revelation of the truth about Argent Energy, and about the Maykrs' complicity in the suffering of their people. title: khan_maykr
body: In [[Doom Eternal]], the Khan Maykr is the leader of the Maykrs, alien beings analogous to angels in many cultures, and has been worshipped as a god by many. Since the stealing of Father from the Maykr homeworld, Urdak, the Khan Maykr has turned to Argent Energy to sustain herself and her race and stave off the process of Transfiguration. Unfortunately, the deal she made for this energy involves sacrificing entire worlds and their people to the forces of Hell.

title: alex_danvers
body:
[b]Alex Danvers[/b] (Full name: Alexandra Danvers) is a character from the CW Network's Supergirl TV series.

She is the older adopted sister of Kara Danvers/[[Supergirl]], who was adopted by the Danvers family after Kara's escape pod landed on Earth years after the destruction of the planet Krypton and was found by her cousin [[Superman]], who handed Kara to the Danvers for safety.

In the show, Alex is an agent of the Department of Extranormal Operations (DEO), a secret government agency tasked with monitoring alien presence on Earth. Despite not being related by blood, both Alex and Kara cared for each other whenever they're in trouble. In season 2, Alex comes out as a Lesbian, who kept her sexuality a secret due to past trauma as a teenager due to being rejected by a girl she had a crush on.

[[Indie virtual youtuber]]. Her original concept and design are based off "a post":[https://warosu.org/jp/thread/28384060#p28385880] from [[4chan]]'s /jp/ board, where an anon recounted a dream he had involving a 6th member of [[Hololive English]]:

[quote]
Just woke up, had a rather vivid /hlgg/ related dream so I'm typing it out before I forget about it:
In the dream a 6th member of holoEN was introduced way later than the others. Her name was "Koopa" and she wasn't much to look at: she had like dirty green hair that reached just past her shoulders and wore very basic almost colorless clothes and she looked constantly very nervous and shy. I was told by my irl boss to support her for some reason, and I had to do that on /hlgg/ where everyone was shitting on her for being boring and never saying anything. I reluctantly had to defend her but I didn't have my keyboard so I had to say all my posts into a telephone that ringed even though I was already talking into it. Any dream specialists here who could tell me what the fuck any of that meant?
[/quote]

title: demon_queen_lilith
body:
Lilith is the Chief Leader of Demon World in [[Guardian Tales]].

She is a charismatic and wise ruler of the Demon World. A long time ago, when she adventured with the previous generation of warriors Kaden and Erina, her cold and calm tendencies made her an excellent comrade for the party. After finishing their adventure, she united the chaotic nation and made herself Queen with her stern and realistic features that make her a perfect leader.

Lilith is assisted by the Old Swordsman Erina. They met each other while Lilith was still a young child and Erina was still an active Warrior. The two of them have been taking care of each other for over hundreds of years as friends and annoying family. It's obvious why Lilith worries about Erina since she has lived past the life expectancy of an average human, but Erina doesn't pay no mind to Lilith's nagging and usually wanders off somewhere. Lilith's desk is rumored to be always neat and free of any objects, because she would end up tossing all them at Erina and breaking everything. However, when Erina is in a dire situation, Lilith would always show up to help. Albeit she nags and clicks her tongue when she arrives

She is famous for taking care of herself. She maintains a strict diet and exercise regimen and is the founder of the famous "Morning Routine for the Success" in Demon World, consisting of waking up early morning, jogging, meditation, and cold showers. She abstains from eating sweets, so when she does, she only allows the best. Lilith is especially strict on the quality of cookies. If there's one thing everyone isn't aware of about perfect Lilith, it's that she is in a constant battle against her less-perfect self. title: ookurikara
body:
A [i][[Touken Ranbu]][/i] character. He is based on the sword of the same name that belonged to the Date clan. The sword initially belonged to the second shogun Hidetada before being bestowed to Date Tadamune. It is the work of the swordsmith Soushuu, though the sword itself does not carry his signature.

His name comes from the Kurikara dragon depicted on the sword, a common representation of the deity Fudou Myou'ou. The dragon appears as a [[tattoo]] on Ookurikara's right arm in human form. He also wears a [[necklace]] with the Sanskrit character "Kan" (खनति), which is said to represent Fudou.

Ookurikara is curt to the Saniwa, and often acts aloof to the rest of the Citadel. He often makes comments about how he does not plan to get along with his master or the other swords. Fans have depicted a much gentler, nicer side to him in spite of his standoffish exterior; this variation is called "Kara-chan", similar to [i][[Kantai Collection]][/i]'s "Nuinui" variation of [[shiranui (kancolle)|Shiranui]].

He is a [[dark-skinned male|dark skinned man]] with [[brown hair]] and [[yellow eyes]]. He wears a black [[jacket]] with a white [[t-shirt]].

Voiced by [[Furukawa Makoto]]. Designed by [[Komo (sleepy)]].

title: aerosmith_(stand)
body:
[[Stand (jojo)|]] power of [[Narancia Ghirga]] from [[JoJo no Kimyou na Bouken]]. Manifests as a miniature airplane with a separate hovering viewfinder over Narancia's eye.

The Stand is controlled by Narancia akin to an RC airplane, and is equipped with miniature machine guns and missiles. The viewfinder tracks targets by their carbon dioxide emissions, but it is ineffective in large crowds. When it fires bullets, Narancia tends to shout "BORA BORA BORA!" and then ends it with "Volare via!"

Namesake is the American rock band [[Aerosmith]].

title: spice_girl_(stand)
body:
[[Stand (jojo)|]] power of [[Trish Una]] from [[JoJo no Kimyou na Bouken]]. Manifests as a feminine pink humanoid decorated with mathematical symbols and is, unlike most Stands, fully sentient.

Possesses the power to "soften" things, increasing their malleability and giving them a rubber-like consistency. Spice Girl can abruptly return the object to its original state, or use its considerable strength to break the object cleanly.

Namesake is the British pop girl group Spice Girls. Screams "WANNABEEEEEE" during its finishing attack, which is the name of one of their songs.

title: sleeper_hold
body:
[[Wrestling]] move.

The wrestler applying the hold positions himself behind his opponent. He then wraps his/her arm around the opponent's neck, pressing the biceps against one side of the neck and the inner bone of the forearm against the other side. The neck is squeezed inside the arm very tightly. Additional pressure can be applied by grabbing the left shoulder with the right hand, or grabbing the biceps of the left arm near the elbow, then using the left hand to push the opponent's head towards the crook of the right elbow.

This move has been popularized by WWE Superstars "Rowdy" Roddy Piper and [[Dolph Ziggler]], both of whom use this as their finishers.

A grounded variation of the sleeper hold, with body scissors applied, is called the [[rear naked choke]] in professional wrestling (though in [[mixed martial arts]], the "rear naked choke" term is used instead of sleeper hold, and whether the body scissors application is present or not).

title: kamura_(armor)
body:
The distinctive starting armor from [[Monster Hunter Rise]]. So called because it's the signature hunter outfit for the monster-hunting warriors of Kamura Village, the player character's home town. 

The design of the set seems to take inspiration from traditional ninja outfits, but with many "hunter" flairs added, such as utility straps and pieces of animal pelt. 

An upgraded edition of the armor exists: the Kamura S Set, which has better stats but an identical appearance.

title: social_distancing
body:
A phrase made commonplace in guidelines published by various governments around the world for mitigation of the [[Coronavirus Pandemic|COVID-19 pandemic]].  "Social distancing" is the practice of maintaining physical separation while interacting with other people.  The exact distance varies from jurisdiction to jurisdiction, but is generally around six feet/two meters.

Use when characters are keeping their distance in a manner that is a clear reference to pandemic life (one visual clue to a pandemic reference is the accompanying wearing of [[mouth mask]]s for no other visible reason).

title: hg_ni_koisuru_futari
body:
Manga series by [[Kudou Makoto]], published in [[Gundam Ace]]. The series follows an [[office lady]] named [[Kanzaki Sayaka (HG ni Koisuru Futari)|]] and a high school girl named [[Takamiya Sora]], who quickly connect over their shared passion for [[gunpla]] [[model kit|models]]. It focuses on the leads' bonding over their shared hobby, experiences with the [[Gundam]] franchise, and having someone to talk about those interests with for the first time.

The series is heavily influenced by the mangaka's own experience watching [[Gundam SEED]] and [[Gundam SEED Destiny|Destiny]] when she was younger, as well as her current love of gunpla.

It is set in the same continuity as Kudou's other ongoing work, [[Bukiyou na Senpai]].

title: super_robot_wars_v
body:
A [[Super Robot Wars]] title released for the series' 25 anniversary in 2017 for [[PlayStation Vita]] and [[PlayStation 4]], and later ported to [[Nintendo Switch]] and Steam in 2019. It is notable for a variety of reasons - it's Southeast Asian release marks the first time a crossover game in the SRW series has had an official English translation, the game's Steam port marks the first official SRW release on PC, and the inclusion of [[Uchuu Senkan Yamato 2199]] marks the first time a non-mecha space opera series has been added to an SRW game.
